Cleaning Data¶

In [ ]:
# Removing url from the content column
df.content=df.content.str.replace(r'http\S+','')
In [16]:
# Convert the texts in content column to lower case
df.content=df.content.str.lower()
In [17]:
# Remove punctuation from the texts in content column
remove_punct=lambda x: x.translate(str.maketrans('', '', string.punctuation))
df.content=df.content.apply(remove_punct)
In [18]:
# Some tweet texts in content column have \n which indicates a new line. This has to be manually removed
df.content=df.content.str.replace('\n','')

# Form a list of stop words to remove from our data
more_words=["u","know","cant","go","dont","na","say","abc","ur","mbujari","amp","lets","dey","pls","\n","hey"]
In [21]:
# Call the python in built stop words
stop_words=set(stopwords.words('english'))
# Update the stop words with 'more_words'
stop_words.update(more_words)
In [22]:
# Function to remove every word in the stop words list from our content column in the dataframe
remove_words=lambda x: ' '.join([word for word in x.split() if word not in stop_words])
In [23]:
# Apply the remove_words function
df["texts"]=df.content.apply(remove_words)

Word Cloud¶

In [30]:
# Plot the word cloud of tweets
word_cloud_texts = " ".join(tweets)
max_words=100
word_cloud = WordCloud(
                    background_color='black',
                    stopwords=set(stop_words),
                    max_words=max_words,
                    max_font_size=30,
                    scale=5,
    colormap='magma',
                    random_state=1).generate(word_cloud_texts)
fig = plt.figure(1, figsize=(35,35))
plt.axis('off')
plt.title('Word Cloud for top '+str(max_words)+' words', fontsize=70,color='green')
fig.subplots_adjust(top=2.3)
plt.imshow(word_cloud)
plt.show()

Sentiment Analysis¶

In [31]:
# Define a function that creates Polarity score for each tweet text
SIA=SentimentIntensityAnalyzer()
polarity_score=lambda x:SIA.polarity_scores(x)
sentiment_scores=df.texts.apply(polarity_score)
In [32]:
# Create dataframe for the polarity scores
sentiments=pd.DataFrame(list(sentiment_scores))
sentiments.columns=['Negative','Positive','Neutral','Compound']
In [33]:
# Create a label for each polarity score
sentiments['Sentiment']=np.where( sentiments['Compound']>0,'Positive','Negative')
sentiments['Sentiment']=np.where(sentiments['Compound']==0,'Neutral',sentiments['Sentiment'])
